#########################
# 			#	
#      RUN SCRIPT       #
#			#
#########################


1) must be started as root, put in the terminal "su -" or sudo su

2) Then assign execute permissions to the script, put "chmod + x configure_linux_1.0.sh"

3) Now run the script "./configure_linux_1.0.sh"

4) In the script, select the GNU Linux, set the username and remain attentive to the installation.




